00:00:04.310 --> 00:00:07.550
On behalf of the Emory
Libraries and the Stuart A. Rose

00:00:07.550 --> 00:00:10.100
Manuscript, Archives,
and Rare Book Library,

00:00:10.100 --> 00:00:14.660
I'm thrilled to welcome you to
tonight's special event, Sister

00:00:14.660 --> 00:00:17.735
Writers: An Evening with
Pearl Cleage and Tayari Jones.

00:00:22.100 --> 00:00:23.570
Round of applause is in order.

00:00:26.330 --> 00:00:27.980
My name is Jennifer Meehan.

00:00:27.980 --> 00:00:31.010
I serve as interim director
of the Rose Library.

00:00:31.010 --> 00:00:35.030
Our mission in the Rose Library
is to collect and connect

00:00:35.030 --> 00:00:39.530
stories of human experience
to promote access and learning

00:00:39.530 --> 00:00:42.290
and to create
opportunities for dialogue

00:00:42.290 --> 00:00:45.440
for all wise hearts
who seek knowledge.

00:00:45.440 --> 00:00:49.550
As part of our mission we offer
programs such as this one,

00:00:49.550 --> 00:00:52.790
and we put on exhibits to
explore and share stories

00:00:52.790 --> 00:00:55.550
from the collections
such as the exhibit which

00:00:55.550 --> 00:00:57.380
inspired this program.

00:00:57.380 --> 00:01:01.100
She Gathers Me: Networks
Among Black Women Writers

00:01:01.100 --> 00:01:04.010
curated by Gabrielle Dudley,
instruction archivist

00:01:04.010 --> 00:01:07.040
in the rose library and
our moderator here tonight.

00:01:09.710 --> 00:01:12.980
Another round of applause.

00:01:12.980 --> 00:01:16.040
She Gathers Me explores the
networks among black women

00:01:16.040 --> 00:01:19.490
writers through an examination
of the connections found

00:01:19.490 --> 00:01:23.450
within their letters, journals,
calendars, and photographs.

00:01:23.450 --> 00:01:25.610
One story explored
in the exhibit

00:01:25.610 --> 00:01:28.190
is the intimate connection
between our guests

00:01:28.190 --> 00:01:29.480
this evening.

00:01:29.480 --> 00:01:32.810
New York Times bestselling
author and new Emory faculty

00:01:32.810 --> 00:01:35.150
member, Tayari Jones--

00:01:35.150 --> 00:01:36.890
[APPLAUSE]

00:01:36.890 --> 00:01:39.850
We're just going
to keep applauding

00:01:39.850 --> 00:01:42.940
--and nationally recognized
playwright, poet, novelist,

00:01:42.940 --> 00:01:45.190
and social activist,
Pearl Cleage,

00:01:45.190 --> 00:01:48.165
whose papers are amongst the
Rose Libraries collections.

00:01:48.165 --> 00:01:51.440
[APPLAUSE]

00:01:53.800 --> 00:01:55.570
In discussion together
they will share

00:01:55.570 --> 00:01:58.150
more of the story of
their intimate connection

00:01:58.150 --> 00:01:59.800
of mentorship and writing.

00:01:59.800 --> 00:02:02.620
We hope that you will visit
this exhibit which is currently

00:02:02.620 --> 00:02:06.020
