inspiration behind that?

00:58:00.820 --> 00:58:02.770
Totally not my choice.

00:58:02.770 --> 00:58:04.640
Didn't have any input
into that at all,

00:58:04.640 --> 00:58:07.390
and actually didn't
like that color at all.

00:58:07.390 --> 00:58:09.480
But people have liked it a lot.

00:58:09.480 --> 00:58:13.690
So I was wrong because
people did embrace it.

00:58:13.690 --> 00:58:14.200
Yeah.

00:58:14.200 --> 00:58:17.590
So oftentimes the
author doesn't have

00:58:17.590 --> 00:58:20.350
much to say about the
cover of the book.

00:58:20.350 --> 00:58:24.000
And that was their
design, not mine.

00:58:24.000 --> 00:58:24.957
But it was all right.

00:58:24.957 --> 00:58:26.290
It did fine and people liked it.

00:58:26.290 --> 00:58:27.345
So it was fine.

00:58:27.345 --> 00:58:28.970
And what'd you ask
me about the other--

00:58:28.970 --> 00:58:30.160
Shero.

00:58:30.160 --> 00:58:30.700
About?

00:58:30.700 --> 00:58:32.270
Shero.

00:58:32.270 --> 00:58:35.730
Like my favorite shero?

00:58:35.730 --> 00:58:38.890
Is Ava my favorite one?

00:58:38.890 --> 00:58:40.890
Of all the women that
I've written about?

00:58:40.890 --> 00:58:42.360
I can't really pick like that.

00:58:42.360 --> 00:58:45.180
I love Ava so much,
but I also love

00:58:45.180 --> 00:58:47.340
some of the other women
who have done other things.

00:58:47.340 --> 00:58:48.507
I love the women in my play.

00:58:48.507 --> 00:58:51.510
So that's kind of like
picking among your kids.

00:58:51.510 --> 00:58:52.302
So I love them all.

00:58:52.302 --> 00:58:53.843
I'd let them all
stay in that circle.

00:58:53.843 --> 00:58:55.220
And one last one for Tayari.

00:58:55.220 --> 00:58:57.950
What's your inspiration
for writing?

00:58:57.950 --> 00:58:59.630
Your inspiration for writing?

00:58:59.630 --> 00:59:00.470
In general?

00:59:00.470 --> 00:59:01.410
Yes.

00:59:01.410 --> 00:59:01.910
Oh.

00:59:01.910 --> 00:59:03.330
It really varies.

00:59:03.330 --> 00:59:05.430
I mean it varies with my mood.

00:59:05.430 --> 00:59:08.630
I think consistently the
inspiration is always

00:59:08.630 --> 00:59:12.560
to try to figure out an answer
to a question that's bothering

00:59:12.560 --> 00:59:16.310
me in my own life and I then
I use the stories to try

00:59:16.310 --> 00:59:17.990
to work it out.

00:59:17.990 --> 00:59:21.727
But I don't write books
about people I know.

00:59:21.727 --> 00:59:23.810
Sometimes people say, who
are these people really?

00:59:23.810 --> 00:59:25.810
And I'm like they're
actually not anyone.

00:59:25.810 --> 00:59:29.270
They think I'm lying, but
they really are imaginary.

00:59:29.270 --> 00:59:31.310
But the questions
that they raise

00:59:31.310 --> 00:59:32.960
tend to come from my own life.

00:59:32.960 --> 00:59:34.160
I'd like to prattle
around in your head.

00:59:34.160 --> 00:59:34.660
OK.

00:59:34.660 --> 00:59:36.740
Thank you so much.

00:59:36.740 --> 00:59:39.650
So we are going to take one
final question over here

00:59:39.650 --> 00:59:41.600
on this side.

00:59:41.600 --> 00:59:42.200
Good evening.

00:59:42.200 --> 00:59:45.890
I just want to seize the
opportunity to say how--

00:59:45.890 --> 00:59:48.258
I can kind of feel your
kind is coming for--

00:59:48.258 --> 00:59:49.550
you probably don't remember me.

00:59:49.550 --> 00:59:53.450
But my mother had passed
away and I met you

00:59:53.450 --> 00:59:55.790
at the Nordan Juice
Bar and I had told you

00:59:55.790 --> 00:59:59.780
about all I wanted was my
mother's letters my father had

00:59:59.780 --> 01:00:01.790
written her from World War II.

01:00:01.790 --> 01:00:04.160
And he must have written
something provocative

01:00:04.160 --> 01:00:07.118
and he would say I
can't wait to get home

01:00:07.118 --> 01:00:08.160
and then he'd cut it out.

01:00:08.160 --> 01:00:11.575
So there was this letter
with all these holes in it.

01:00:11.575 --> 01:00:13.700
And so you said, you know
that's a book, don't you?

01:00:13.700 --> 01:00:14.420
And I said, it is?

01:00:14.420 --> 01:00:15.920
And you said I'm
going on book tour.

01:00:15.920 --> 01:00:18.398
Write something and when
I get back I'll help you.

01:00:18.398 --> 01:00:19.940
So I used to see
you out and I'd hide

01:00:19.940 --> 01:00:21.315
because I hadn't
written anything

01:00:21.315 --> 01:00:23.870
and you said I'm not going
to bug you about writing.

01:00:23.870 --> 01:00:25.580
If you want to
write I'll help you.

01:00:25.580 --> 01:00:27.080
And I just thought
that was so kind.

01:00:27.080 --> 01:00:28.788
And then one time you
said the material--

01:00:28.788 --> 01:00:31.402
Do you mind add going for
it with your question?

01:00:31.402 --> 01:00:33.110
I just wanted to thank
her for being kind

01:00:33.110 --> 01:00:34.480
and I'd never got started.

01:00:34.480 --> 01:00:37.850
But since I saw how
you mentored her

01:00:37.850 --> 01:00:40.640
I really would take the
opportunity to write.

01:00:40.640 --> 01:00:42.410
It's been very inspiring to me.

01:00:42.410 --> 01:00:44.060
Thank you.

